              "content": "Heart Rate (HR): HR = # of beats in 15 sec. x 4 (Normal: 60-100 beats/min). Assess pulse strength: strong, weak, thready, slow, or irregular.\nRespiration Rate (RR): RR = # of chest rises in 15 sec. x 4 (Normal: 12-20 breaths/min). Listen for abnormal breath sounds (wheezing, rales, stridor), coughing, or labored breathing.\nBlood Pressure (BP): Assess strength of radial pulse. Strong \u2248 100 mmHg, Weak \u2248 80 mmHg, None = < 80 mmHg.\nLevel of Responsiveness (AVPU): Using AVPU scale - Alert and Oriented (A&O) to person, place, time, and event; Verbal stimuli; Pain Stimuli; Unresponsive.\nPupils Equal Round Reactive to Light (PERRL): Assess pupil size, equality, and reactivity.\nSkin Color \u2022 Temperature \u2022 Moisture (SCTM): Assess color (pink, red, pale, blue, yellow), temperature (warm, hot, cold), and moisture (sweating, dry, diaphoretic).\nCirculation \u2022 Sensory \u2022 Motor (CSM): Assess distal pulses and capillary refill, sensation, and motor function on all four extremities.",
