              "content": "Signs/Symptoms (S/Sx)",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Anxiety & denial\nChest pain/pressure\nPain that radiates to the left jaw and arm\nShortness of breath (SOB)\nWeakness\nPale skin\nDiaphoresis (sweating profusely)\nPossible elevated HR and RR\nS/Sx often resolves with rest and/or nitroglycerin",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "content": "Some individuals may simply present with weakness, nausea and/or pain in the back and/or belly.",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Myocardial Infarction (MI)",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Signs/Symptoms (S/Sx)",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Anxiety & denial\nNausea & vomiting\nChest pain/pressure\nPain that radiates to the left jaw and arm\nShortness of breath (SOB)\nWeakness\nPale cool & clammy\nDiaphoresis (sweating profusely)\nElevated HR & RR\nCardiogenic shock especially if on betablockers and CCBs",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "note",
              "content": "Some individuals may simply present with weakness, nausea and/or pain in the back and/or belly.",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Congestive Heart Failure (CHF)",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Signs/Symptoms (S/Sx)",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Weakness & fatigue\nNausea & vomiting\nSwollen ankles and legs or shortness of breath due to pulmonary edema (crackly lung sounds)\nMay have chest pain\nIncreased HR & RR",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Treatment (Tx)",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 4,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "General Treatment:",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Rest\nPosition of comfort\n325 mg of Aspirin\nPatient's Rx of nitroglycerin\nCPR when indicated\nEvacuate immediately!",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
