    {
      "moduleTitle": "Stroke (CVA)",
      "moduleSubtitle": "================================================================================",
      "category": "Medical",
      "iconName": "brain.head.profile",
      "description": "Recognition, FAST Assessment, and Treatment",
      "orderIndex": 6,
      "location": null,
      "sections": [
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Introduction",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 0,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Recognition, FAST Assessment, and Treatment\nLocation: Mount Rainier National Park, Washington",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "What is a Stroke (CVA)?",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 1,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "A CVA (stroke) occurs when either a blood clot lodges in a cerebral blood vessel (ischemic stroke) or a cerebral artery ruptures (hemorrhagic stroke), both leading to inadequate tissue perfusion of the brain.",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Neurological damage from an ischemic stroke might be reversible with thrombolytics, which dissolve clots to improve blood flow and prevent permanent brain damage. This therapy is for certain patients and must be administered within a 4.5-hour window after symptom onset.",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "A stroke has sudden onset. It is critical to determine a \"Last Seen Normal\" time from the patient or bystanders. Proper wilderness treatment involves accurate assessment, patient comfort, and prompt evacuation.",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Aphasia",
              "orderIndex": 3,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Aphasia is an impairment of language, common in strokes and other brain injuries. It can present in three ways: 1) inability to form words and speak while understanding others, 2) inability to comprehend language resulting in incomprehensible speech, or 3) a combination of both. Individuals who can comprehend language might still communicate in written form.",
              "orderIndex": 4,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Signs and Symptoms",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Headache\nSlurred speech\nHemiparesis (one-sided weakness)\nHemiplegia (paralysis on one side of the body)\nLoss of CSM on one side (Circulation, Sensation, Movement)\nAphasia\nDifficulty breathing\nDecreased AVPU (Level of Responsiveness)",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "FAST Assessment",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "F - Facial Droop",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Partial paralysis of one side of the face results in drooping features. Instruction: Ask the person to smile.",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "A - Arm Drift",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "The person cannot raise or hold arms up equally. Instruction: Ask the person to hold both arms straight out in front of them with palms up.",
              "orderIndex": 3,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "S - Speech",
              "orderIndex": 4,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "The person slurs words, uses the wrong words or is unable to speak. There may also be difficulty swallowing exhibited by coughing or choking. Instruction: Ask the person to repeat a sentence after you.",
              "orderIndex": 5,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "T - Time",
              "orderIndex": 6,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Time lost is brain lost. Think 'Brain Attack', like 'Heart Attack'. Instructions: Ask family/friends/bystanders when the person was last seen acting normally. Evacuate immediately!!",
              "orderIndex": 7,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Treatment",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 4,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Tx (Treatment):",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "ABCs (Airway, Breathing, Circulation)\nAssess & document \"FAST\" (Face drooping, Arm weakness, Speech difficulty, Time to call emergency services)\nReassurance\nEvacuate immediately!",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "warning",
              "content": "NEVER give aspirin in the event of a CVA. It will increase bleeding in the brain in the case of a hemorrhagic stroke.",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "moduleTitle": "Hypothermia",
      "moduleSubtitle": "================================================================================",
      "category": "Environmental",
      "iconName": "thermometer.snowflake",
      "description": "Stages, Recognition, and Treatment",
      "orderIndex": 7,
      "location": null,
      "sections": [
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Introduction",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 0,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Stages, Recognition, and Treatment\nLocation: Denali National Park, Alaska",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Assessing Hypothermia",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 1,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Assessment Steps:",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "numberedList",
              "content": "1. Assess Consciousness (conscious or unresponsive)\n2. Assess Movement (normal, impaired, or no movement)\n3. Assess Shivering (mild, uncontrollable, or decreasing)\n4. Assess AVPU (A&Ox4, decreasing, \"U\" on AVPU)",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Stages of Hypothermia",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "COLD STRESSED",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Indicators:",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "CONSCIOUS\nMOVEMENT NORMAL\nSHIVERING\nAVPU = A&Ox4 (Level of Responsiveness = Alert & Oriented x4)",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment:\n1. Reduce heat loss\n2. Provide high-calorie food or drink\n3. Move around/exercise to warm up",
              "orderIndex": 3,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "MILD",
              "orderIndex": 4,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Indicators:",
              "orderIndex": 5,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "CONSCIOUS\nIMPAIRED MOVEMENT\nSHIVERING\nAVPU = A&Ox4",
              "orderIndex": 6,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment:\n1. Handle gently\n2. Have patient sit or lie down in hypowrap for at least 30 min.\n3. Heat sources - chest, back, armpits\n4. Give high-calorie food/drink\n5. Monitor for 'afterdrop' if patient recovers\n6. Evacuate if no improvement",
              "orderIndex": 7,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "MODERATE",
              "orderIndex": 8,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Indicators:",
              "orderIndex": 9,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "CONSCIOUS\nUNCONTROLLABLE SHIVERING \u2192 NONE\n\u2193AVPU (decreasing Level of Responsiveness)",
              "orderIndex": 10,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment:\n1. No standing/walking\n2. Handle gently\n3. Keep horizontal in hypowrap\n4. Heat sources - chest, back, armpits\n5. No food or drink\n6. Evacuate carefully to hospital with ECLS capability",
              "orderIndex": 11,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "SEVERE",
              "orderIndex": 12,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "If cold & unresponsive, assume SEVERE HYPOTHERMIA",
              "orderIndex": 13,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment:\n1. Check carotid pulse for 60 sec.",
              "orderIndex": 14,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "IF no pulse, start CPR\nIF pulse but no breathing, rescue breathe: (1 breath every 5-6 sec.)",
              "orderIndex": 15,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "numberedList",
              "content": "2. Treat like Moderate Hypothermia\n3. Evacuate carefully ASAP to hospital with ECLS capability",
              "orderIndex": 16,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "moduleTitle": "Skin Related Problems",
      "moduleSubtitle": "================================================================================",
      "category": "Minor Issues",
      "iconName": "hand.raised.fill",
      "description": "Poison Ivy, Oak, Sumac, and Fungal Infections",
      "orderIndex": 8,
      "location": null,
      "sections": [
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Introduction",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 0,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Poison Ivy, Oak, Sumac, and Fungal Infections\nLocation: Great Smoky Mountains National Park, North Carolina/Tennessee",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Poison Ivy, Oak & Sumac",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Toxicodendron Genus",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 1,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Contact dermatitis caused by plants in the Toxicodendron genus. Urushiol-induced contact dermatitis can be severe (potential for anaphylaxis). Approximately 15-30% of people are non-allergic. Risk of inhaling fumes from burning plants. Toxicodendron sp. is found across the US and southern Canada, excluding deserts and altitudes above ~5000 ft (1524 m).",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Prevention",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Recognize plants by \"leaves of three\"\nWear protective clothing\nWash exposed clothing with laundry detergent or special solvents like Tecnu\u00ae products",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Signs/Symptoms (S/Sx)",
              "orderIndex": 3,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Extremely itchy, red rash containing small to large fluid-filled blisters\nOutbreaks can last up to three weeks\nDifficulty breathing from inhalation of fumes from burning the plant",
              "orderIndex": 4,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment (Tx)",
              "orderIndex": 5,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "numberedList",
              "content": "1. Wash exposed area immediately with soap and cold water (avoiding hot water to prevent pore opening and faster absorption)\n2. Use Tecnu Extreme\u00ae for its oil-dissolving and anti-itch properties\n3. Consider anti-histamines or oral steroids for severe reactions",
              "orderIndex": 6,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "warning",
              "content": "Evacuate anyone who has inhaled fumes or has difficulty breathing.",
              "orderIndex": 7,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sectionTitle": "Fungal Infections",
          "subtitle": null,
          "orderIndex": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Fungal infections typically grow in dark, warm, moist areas like feet and groin.",
              "orderIndex": 0,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Prevention",
              "orderIndex": 1,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Wear breathable, dry clothing\nFrequently change socks and underwear to reduce moisture in problem areas",
              "orderIndex": 2,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "Signs/Symptoms (S/Sx)",
              "orderIndex": 3,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": "Red, swollen, itchy, skin that can be scaling and cracking",
              "orderIndex": 4,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "procedure",
              "content": "Treatment (Tx)",
              "orderIndex": 5,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "numberedList",
              "content": "1. Clean and air-dry the affected area\n2. Allow it to breathe\n3. Short exposure to UV radiation may help\n4. Apply diluted tea tree oil, 1% hydrocortisone cream, or other over-the-counter anti-fungal creams",
              "orderIndex": 6,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "================================================================================\nEND OF MODULES\n================================================================================",
              "orderIndex": 7,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "This extraction represents a comprehensive migration from chapter-based reference material to modern, topic-based modules with rebranding to Black Elk Mountain Medicine and terminology updates (SOAA'P \u2192 SOAPNote).",
              "orderIndex": 8,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": "All modules include randomized scenario locations from US National and State Parks for enhanced learning and scenario realism.",
              "orderIndex": 9,
              "metadata": null,
              "location": null
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
